TY  - JOUR
AU  - Khwaja, Asim Ijaz
AU  - Mian, Atif
AU  - Zia, Bilal
T1  - Dollars Dollars Everywhere, Nor Any Dime to Lend: Credit Limit Constraints on Financial Sector Absorptive Capacity
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhq091
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 23
IS  - 12
SP  - 4281
EP  - 4323
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We exploit an unexpected inflow of liquidity in an emerging market to study how capital is intermediated to firms. We find that backward-looking credit limit constraints imposed by banks make it difficult for firms to borrow, despite readily available bank liquidity, healthy aggregate demand, and a sharply falling cost of capital. The resulting aggregate failure to extend and retain capital in the economy suggests that agency costs that force banks to rely on sticky balance-sheet-based credit limits prevent emerging economies from effectively intermediating capital.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhq091
ER  - 



